A.2 CIRCULATION RULES (these set the MINIMUM room footprint)
A room must accommodate not just the furniture but also the aisles and
clearances around it. Violating these makes the room unusable.

- Primary walking aisle (corridor / hallway):              ≥ 0.90 m
- Secondary aisle (between sofa and coffee table):         ≥ 0.40 m
- Pulled-out dining / desk chair clearance:                ≥ 0.70 m
- Both sides of a bed (each side, for getting in/out):     ≥ 0.60 m
                              (single-occupancy bed needs only ONE side)
- In front of an open wardrobe / closet door:              ≥ 0.75 m
- In front of an open kitchen appliance / fridge:          ≥ 1.00 m
- Around a dining table (each side):                       ≥ 0.90 m
- Sofa-to-TV viewing distance (rule of thumb 2× screen W): ≥ 2.00 m
- Doorway swing radius (in front of an inswing door):      ≥ 0.90 m

